This book feels like a condensed argument by John C. Bogle endorsing Index Fund investing. The main idea is simple and easy to understand, supported by many arguments in each chapters. Get the book here.
About The Author John C. &ldquo;Jack&rdquo; Bogle was the man who popularised Index Fund investing. Applauded by Warren Buffet &ldquo;&hellip;has probably done more for the American investor than any man in the country.&rdquo;
Takeaways It is better to buy stocks that are listed in an index fund and hold it for a long time.
